Scotland fullback Stuart Hogg was named Six Nations player of the championship on Thursday for the second year in a row.The 24-year-old scored three tries, including a double during the opening weekend victory against Ireland.He continued to be his team&#8217;s main attacking threat throughout the tournament, playing a key role as the Scots went on to secure wins over Wales and Italy.Hogg secured 24 percent of the public vote with Ireland back-row forward CJ Stander in second place.&#8220;To receive this award again is an absolute honour, particularly when you take other players on the shortlist into account,&#8221; Hogg said.-Reuters